data.name: Crispy Tofu with Broccoli and Garlic Sauce
data.quickTastyDescription: A quick and delicious plant-based meal featuring crispy tofu and vibrant broccoli in a savory garlic sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: Press the tofu for 15 minutes to remove excess moisture.
Cut the tofu into cubes and toss in cornstarch, salt, and pepper.
Heat olive oil in a pan over medium-high heat and add the tofu cubes.
Cook until crispy and golden brown on all sides, about 8-10 minutes.
While the tofu cooks, steam or microwave the broccoli until tender, about 3-4 minutes.
In a small bowl, mix soy sauce, minced garlic, and a splash of water.
Once tofu is crispy, add the broccoli to the pan, pour the garlic sauce over everything, and stir-fry for another 2-3 minutes.
